.\" Man page template for copypaste(1).
.\" Generated/updated by scripts/gen-manpage.sh — DO NOT EDIT THE GENERATED .1 BY HAND.
.\" Placeholders: @VERSION@, @DATE@, @COMMANDS@
.TH COPYPASTE 1 "@DATE@" "CopyPaste @VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
copypaste \- clipboard history CLI for the CopyPaste daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B copypaste
.RI [ COMMAND ]
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B copypaste
is the command-line interface to the CopyPaste clipboard-history daemon.
It connects to the running daemon over a local Unix socket and lets you
inspect, search, copy, export, import, and clear clipboard history,
toggle private (pause) mode, and watch new items in real time.
.PP
The daemon must be running for most commands to succeed.
See \fBcopypastectl\fR(1) or the project README for daemon management.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help for \fBcopypaste\fR or a specific subcommand.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.SH COMMANDS
@COMMANDS@
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
List the 20 most recent clipboard items:
.B copypaste list --limit 20
.TP
Search history for "password":
.B copypaste search password
.TP
Copy the most recent item back to the system clipboard:
.B copypaste copy 1
.TP
Copy by UUID:
.B copypaste copy --id 8f3e1c2a-...
.TP
Export the last 1000 items to JSON:
.B copypaste export --output history.json
.TP
Pause recording (private mode):
.B copypaste private on
.TP
Watch for new items in real time:
.B copypaste watch --interval 1000
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/copypaste.sock
Unix socket used to talk to the daemon (Linux).
.TP
.I $TMPDIR/copypaste.sock
Unix socket on macOS.
.TP
.I $XDG_DATA_HOME/copypaste/history.db
SQLite database storing clipboard history.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/copypaste/config.toml
Optional user configuration.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Generic error (daemon unreachable, invalid argument, I/O failure, etc.).
A human-readable message is printed to standard error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR copypastectl (1),
.BR pbcopy (1),
.BR pbpaste (1),
.BR xclip (1),
.BR wl-copy (1)
.PP
Project homepage: https://github.com/dmytroyevs/copypaste
